''See also'' '''[[Frank]]'''

==English==

===Etymology 1===
From French ''franc'', "free", in turn from the name of an early germanic confederation, ''[[w:Franks|The Franks]]''.

====Adjective====
'''frank''' (''[[comparative]]'' '''franker''', ''[[superlative]]'' '''frankest''')

#[[Honest]], especially in an manner that seems slightly [[blunt]].
#:''May I be frank with you?''

====Verb====
'''frank'''

#To stamp a letter using a printed franking machine.

===Etymology 2===
Shortened form of [[frankfurter]].

====Noun====
'''frank'''
#A [[hot dog]] or [[sausage]].
#:''Buy a package of '''franks''' for the barbecue.''

